Suppose \(f\) is a function which satisfies the properties:

$PAR

\(f(x+y) = f(x) + f(y) + x^2y +xy^2\)

$PAR  for all real numbers \(x\) and \(y\), and 

$PAR\(\displaystyle \lim_{x \to 0} \frac{f(x)}{x} = 1 \).

$PAR \(f'(x) = \) \{ans_rule(40)\}

$PAR

END_TEXT
