       $PAR $BBOLD Hint: $EBOLD Use the definition of a derivative: \(f'(x) = \displaystyle \lim_{h \to 0} \frac{f(x+h)-f(x)}{h} \).  Notice how you can rearrange the formula for \(f(x+y)\) as: \(f(x+y)-f(x) = f(y) + x^2y+xy^2\).  
      END_TEXT
